    {"name": "Sudden infant death syndrome",
     "aliases": ["SIDS", "cot death", "sudden unexplained death in infancy", "crib death"],
     "summary": "Sudden, unexplained death of an infant <1 year after thorough investigation (autopsy, death scene investigation, medical history review). Peak: 2–4 months. Risk factors: prone sleeping (major modifiable risk - 'Back to Sleep' campaign ↓SIDS by 50%), soft bedding, overheating, parental smoking, bed-sharing (especially with alcohol), prematurity, male sex. Protective factors: supine sleeping, breastfeeding, pacifier use, room sharing (not bed-sharing). Pathophysiology: triple risk model - vulnerable infant + critical developmental period + exogenous stressor (prone sleeping, hypoxia). Investigation: must exclude NAI, metabolic disease, infection."},
